# Keep the Docker build context small and safe. Without this file, `COPY . .`
# in Dockerfile pulls in venv/ (~2.5GB), node_modules, the SQLite audit log
# (which may contain real prompts from local testing — possible PII leak into
# any published image), and a pile of dev-only artifacts.

# --- Dependencies (rebuilt inside the image) ---
node_modules
**/node_modules
venv
.venv
env
ENV
__pycache__
**/__pycache__
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.egg-info

# --- Build / test output ---
dist
build
test-results
playwright-report
.pytest_cache
.mypy_cache
.ruff_cache
coverage
htmlcov
.tox

# --- Runtime state (per-deployment, mounted as volume on the server) ---
# data/ holds agentic_demo.db (audit log) + uploaded RAG files. Baking this
# into the image would leak local-testing prompts/responses + persist as
# read-only. The container reads/writes data/ via a host bind mount instead.
data

# --- Local dev / IDE / OS ---
.git
.github
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.gitleaksignore
.editorconfig
.vscode
.idea
.cursor
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
._*
Thumbs.db

# --- Secrets / env (set via runtime env vars, never baked in) ---
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# --- Tests + dev-only docs not needed at runtime ---
tests
e2e
playwright.config.ts
designdocs
docs
Docker.md
SETUP_INSTRUCTIONS.md
CHANGELOG.md
RELEASE_NOTES.md
pytest.ini
requirements-dev.txt

# --- Claude / Oracle / agent memory (private; not part of the demo) ---
ψ
.claude
CLAUDE.md
ONBOARDING.md
